item.description:
@pplsuqbawlz wrote:

[quote=“Ollie, post:2, topic:274147”]What exactly are we supposed to crack?

[quote]java CrackMev2
You Own all. Laugh at the Microsoft noob right away![/quote][/quote]

Right.

import java.io.PrintStream;

public class CrackMev2
{
    public static void main(String args[])
    {
        String s = System.getProperty("os.name");
        if (s != null && s.equals(WIN_AA))
            System.err.println("You Fail, Your OS is neally 15 years old!");
        if (s != null && s.equals(WIN_BB))
            System.err.println("Windows 98 = Fail, DOS is Epic Fail");
        if (s != null && s.equals(WIN_CC))
            System.err.println("If you can display this message I'm suprised your Mistake Edition OS managed it.");
        if (s != null && s.equals(WIN_DD))
            System.err.println("Really. You just managed to avoid Fail");
        if (s != null && s.equals(WIN_EE))
            System.err.println("DOS Fail, your duo on 31st December 1999 failed aswell");
        if (s != null && s.equals(WIN_FF))
            System.err.println("You Win!, Linux still owns you though.");
        if (s != null && s.equals(WIN_GG))
            System.err.println("Epic Fail, GTFO");
        if (s != null && s.equals(WIN_HH))
            System.err.println("Why?");
        if (s != null && s.startsWith(LIN_BB))
            System.err.println("Your a cheapskate noob, Get a proper Linux OS");
        if (s.startsWith(LIN_FF) || s.startsWith(LIN_AA) || s.startsWith(LIN_CC) || s.startsWith(LIN_DD) || s.startsWith(LIN_EE) || s.startsWith(LIN_FF) || s.startsWith(LIN_GG) || s.startsWith(LIN_HH))
            System.out.println("You Own all. Laugh at the Microsoft noob right away!");
        else
            System.err.println("This is statement is true.");
    }

    public static String WIN_AA = "Windows 95";
    public static String WIN_BB = "Windows 98";
    public static String WIN_CC = "Windows Me";
    public static String WIN_DD = "Windows NT";
    public static String WIN_EE = "Windows 2000";
    public static String WIN_FF = "Windows XP";
    public static String WIN_GG = "Windows Vista";
    public static String WIN_HH = "Windows 7";
    public static String LIN_AA = "Linux";
    public static String LIN_BB = "Ubuntu";
    public static String LIN_CC = "DSL";
    public static String LIN_DD = "Gentoo";
    public static String LIN_EE = "Arch";
    public static String LIN_FF = "Cent";
    public static String LIN_GG = "Mac";
    public static String LIN_HH = "Free";

}
